President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Pauline Maier as a member of the Board of Trustees of the James Madison Memorial Fellowship Foundation. Maier is a professor of American History at MIT and has written several books on American history. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Joan W. Harris as a member of the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board. Harris is the President of The Irving Harris Foundation and has served on various cultural organization boards. Additionally, Dallas L. Salisbury will be appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee to the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation. Salisbury is the President and CEO of the Employee Benefit Research Institute and has been involved in various financial education campaigns.